From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Zebrafish <zebrafish@buildroot>
Date: Sun, 17 May 2026 19:23:21 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] crun: link libocispec directly in crun binary

When building with shared libraries (--enable-shared), libcrun.so
is built with a version script (libcrun.lds) that hides all symbols
except libcrun_*, runtime_spec_*, free_runtime_spec_*, and
make_runtime_spec_*. The json_gen_* functions from libocispec,
which are needed by crun's oci_features.c, are thus hidden and
unavailable during linking of the crun binary.

Add libocispec/libocispec.la to crun_LDADD so the json_gen_*
symbols are available to the crun binary. This matches the pattern
already used by tests_tests_libcrun_fuzzer_LDADD.

Upstream-Status: Submitted
Signed-off-by: Zebrafish <zebrafish@buildroot>
diff --git a/Makefile.am b/Makefile.am
index 26c8a1a..e443b77 100644
--- a/Makefile.am
+++ b/Makefile.am
@@ -113,7 +113,7 @@ endif
 else
-crun_LDADD = libcrun.la $(FOUND_LIBS) $(JSON_C_LIBS)
+crun_LDADD = libcrun.la libocispec/libocispec.la $(FOUND_LIBS) $(JSON_C_LIBS)
 if ENABLE_COVERAGE
 crun_LDFLAGS = $(CRUN_LDFLAGS) $(COVERAGE_LDFLAGS)
 else
